VerdeNFC Privacy Policy

Bernd Trappe

Please take a moment to familiarize yourself with my privacy practices and contact me if you have any questions.


What information I collect

My primary purpose in collecting information is improving app stability.
The app itself works locally only, the only network access is required if you open remote files using the file picker.
The only purpose of NFC reading/writing functionality is reading or writing NFC tags which is the main prupose of this app.

1. Personal Information

I do not collect any Personal Information about you. “Personal Information” means personally identifiable information, such as your name, email address, physical address, calendar entries, contact entries, files, photos, call logs, message logs, social media account information , etc.

2. Non-Personal Information

I do not directly collect non-personal information about your use of my App. “Non-Personal Information” means information that is of an anonymous nature, such as the type of mobile device you use, your mobile devices unique device ID, the IP address of your mobile device, your mobile operating system, and information about the way you use the Applications. 
Apple may provide me app crash dumps or reports if you explicitly allow this.

3. Information collected by our Third Party Advertising Partners

I do not include any advertising features.


